WEBVTT

00:00.752 --> 00:02.718
- Good morning, gentlemen.
- Hi.

00:02.787 --> 00:03.886
Max, how'd you sleep?

00:03.953 --> 00:06.355
Oh, I love crashing here!

00:06.424 --> 00:08.431
This is just like college...

00:08.466 --> 00:11.284
staying up too late,
passing out on the couch,

00:11.319 --> 00:13.238
mean Asian chick down the hall.

00:13.273 --> 00:14.559
Yeah. Where is Lily?

00:14.594 --> 00:16.315
I don't know. S-School, maybe?

00:16.350 --> 00:18.035
- I'm right here.
- Oh.

00:19.236 --> 00:21.503
We met Max in Amsterdam
on what we thought

00:21.571 --> 00:24.372
was a tour of pottery cafes, so...

00:24.441 --> 00:26.708
I don't remember much about it,
but I do remember thinking

00:26.776 --> 00:29.010
he was the funniest person
I've ever met.

00:29.048 --> 00:30.982
And we told him
if he ever came into town,

00:31.050 --> 00:34.785
that he had to stay with us.
And I-I-I'm so glad he said yes

00:34.820 --> 00:37.106
because I remember
being really, uh, paranoid

00:37.141 --> 00:38.146
that he didn't like me.

00:39.099 --> 00:40.899
You two, get out of here.

00:40.968 --> 00:42.234
I'm gonna whip us up some breakfast.

00:42.303 --> 00:43.735
Oh!

00:43.804 --> 00:45.037
Oof.

00:45.105 --> 00:47.906
Whoo! My head feels like the Hindenburg.

00:47.975 --> 00:50.676
Oh, come on!

00:50.744 --> 00:52.622
I feel like he was funnier in Europe.

00:52.647 --> 00:54.713
Yeah.

00:54.782 --> 00:56.248
Mitchell! Look!

00:56.317 --> 00:58.183
Our crazy-expensive bottle of wine?

00:58.252 --> 01:00.619
I... uh, we were saving this for the
perfect occasion.

01:00.688 --> 01:04.388
Okay, well, he must've drank it
after we went to bed. Who does that?

01:04.458 --> 01:07.859
Just drinks somebody's most
expensive bottle of wine without asking?

01:07.928 --> 01:09.461
- Okay, it's a hate crime.
- How is it a hate crime?

01:09.530 --> 01:10.896
Because I hate him.

01:10.965 --> 01:13.398
I ca... I can't
believe it's almost gone.

01:13.467 --> 01:15.867
Look, you know, I've only ever
considered opening that twice...

01:15.936 --> 01:17.169
once early
on election night

01:17.237 --> 01:18.971
and then when we thought
"La La Land" won Best Picture.

01:19.039 --> 01:21.306
- I know. It's been a rough year.
- MAX: Breakfast!

01:23.610 --> 01:25.310
No, no.

01:25.379 --> 01:26.379
Is that our caviar?

01:26.447 --> 01:29.514
Yeah! Lucky I found it.
It was hiding in the back of the fridge.

01:29.583 --> 01:31.049
For a special occasion.

01:31.118 --> 01:33.185
- Something wrong?
- Yeah... yeah.

01:33.253 --> 01:35.420
Uh, first you open up
our $400 bottle of wine,

01:35.489 --> 01:37.856
now it's our $200 tin of caviar.

01:37.925 --> 01:39.591
- We were saving those.
- For what?

01:39.660 --> 01:41.126
A celebration, like...

01:41.195 --> 01:42.627
What about when
"Moonlight" won the Oscar?

01:42.696 --> 01:44.663
Okay, it was a big moment
for the community, yes...

01:44.732 --> 01:47.599
Okay, you know what? Look.
I'm gonna go, okay?

01:47.668 --> 01:51.003
But, guys, don't defer enjoyment,

01:51.071 --> 01:53.538
'cause you never know when
you're gonna bite it.

01:53.607 --> 01:56.641
I say, make every night special.

01:56.710 --> 01:58.977
Okay, well, that's a...
that's a fun philosophy,

01:59.046 --> 02:00.312
but not everyone can follow that, okay?

02:00.381 --> 02:02.114
'Cause... 'Cause we have
responsibilities.

02:02.182 --> 02:05.150
We have... We have budgets.
We have a daughter, you know.

02:05.219 --> 02:06.385
Where is our daughter?

02:06.453 --> 02:08.053
- I don't know. Backyard, maybe?
- Maybe.

02:15.472 --> 02:20.472
Synced and corrected by BLuk
www.addic7ed.com

02:20.934 --> 02:25.370
Earl Chambers, my former business
partner-turned dumbass nemesis,

02:25.439 --> 02:27.372
bought the old horizontal wardrobe.

02:27.441 --> 02:30.075
For you closet non-pros,
that means he died.

02:30.144 --> 02:34.179
Then last week, I received
this urn and this note.

02:34.248 --> 02:38.283
"You know what to do with my ashes.
Follow the path."

02:38.352 --> 02:40.419
What the hell does that mean?

02:40.487 --> 02:43.121
You think you can drive me nuts,
but you can't.

02:43.190 --> 02:45.657
He can't actually hear you
unless you open the lid.

02:45.726 --> 02:47.893
I still can't figure out
the meaning of "Follow the path!"

02:47.961 --> 02:49.361
I'm gonna need you to call Shirl

02:49.430 --> 02:51.530
and find out why her father's
been torturing me.

02:51.598 --> 02:53.331
- You call her!
- That's not an option.

02:53.400 --> 02:55.600
She's a greasy slimebucket,
just like her father,

02:55.669 --> 02:57.269
and for some reason,
she doesn't like me.

02:57.337 --> 02:59.504
Hmm... I'll see what I can do.

03:06.780 --> 03:08.413
Oh...

03:08.482 --> 03:10.415
Hey, Manny! What's up?

03:10.484 --> 03:11.917
I'm not here! Everything's fine!

03:11.985 --> 03:14.386
- Super-dupes.
- Okay, I'll... I'll... I'll talk.

03:14.455 --> 03:17.289
Luke and I went to a sketchy
neighborhood for tacos last night,

03:17.357 --> 03:19.424
and he disappeared,
and I haven't seen him since.

03:19.493 --> 03:21.126
What? Where did you see him last?

03:21.195 --> 03:22.360
He went off with this girl.

03:22.379 --> 03:23.395
- With a girl?
- Yeah.

03:23.464 --> 03:25.530
Manny.

03:25.599 --> 03:27.766
Let me tell you a little
something about Dunphy men.

03:27.835 --> 03:29.534
When we come into contact with a lady,

03:29.603 --> 03:31.236
we leave her with a burning sensation.

03:31.305 --> 03:32.704
Let me try that again.

03:32.773 --> 03:35.707
Um... when a Dunphy man
sees a sexy skirt,

03:35.776 --> 03:36.942
he's just gotta get in it.

03:37.010 --> 03:38.243
- No!
- I get the point.

03:38.312 --> 03:39.978
Look, I'm just glad you came to me...

03:40.047 --> 03:41.580
I didn't. You caught me here.

03:41.648 --> 03:43.949
...'cause I don't want Claire
freaking out about this.

03:44.017 --> 03:46.051
Luke's phone is going
straight to voicemail.

03:47.187 --> 03:49.054
Someone's got a sock
on the digital doorknob.

03:49.123 --> 03:51.289
I really think you should be
a little worried about this.

03:51.358 --> 03:52.557
Worried?!

03:52.626 --> 03:54.092
Let me tell you something
about Dunphy men.

03:54.161 --> 03:56.595
Phil, this was
a pretty rough neighborhood.

03:56.663 --> 03:58.897
Tell you what,
if it makes you feel better,

03:58.966 --> 04:00.465
we'll go down there
and look around for him.

04:00.534 --> 04:03.001
We're gonna need backup...
serious backup.

04:05.005 --> 04:06.605
Okay, be cool.

04:06.673 --> 04:08.206
I used to live in this neighborhood.

04:08.275 --> 04:10.542
If you act tough,
nobody will mess with you.

04:11.945 --> 04:12.945
MAN: Hey!

04:14.615 --> 04:15.714
Would you like to try

04:15.782 --> 04:17.949
a cruelty-free
alkaline-water snow cone?

04:18.017 --> 04:19.517
- What?
- Free sample.

04:19.586 --> 04:21.086
You can get a larger one
down at our stand.

04:21.154 --> 04:22.287
We also refurbish tubas.

04:22.356 --> 04:23.855
No, thank you.

04:23.924 --> 04:25.624
What happened to my neighborhood?

04:25.692 --> 04:27.392
Have the best day.

04:28.428 --> 04:31.563
White people with beards...
they ruined everything.

04:31.632 --> 04:34.032
Why would you even say that
this place was dangerous?

04:34.101 --> 04:36.801
It was a lot scarier at dark.
There was jazz.

04:38.972 --> 04:40.338
Luke's still not answering.

04:40.407 --> 04:41.907
We're gonna find him, Phil.

04:41.975 --> 04:43.675
Oh, I-I'm not worried. I've been there.

04:43.744 --> 04:45.877
Meet a girl, you lose track
of place and time,

04:45.946 --> 04:47.546
not just 'cause your
compass watch is missing,

04:47.614 --> 04:49.514
and suddenly her cousin Rodney
has the exact same watch

04:49.583 --> 04:50.815
but swears it was always his.

04:50.884 --> 04:53.185
Oh, look! Mario's Bodyshop.

04:53.253 --> 04:55.720
At least one thing is still the same.

04:55.791 --> 04:57.491
There's nothing that happens
in this street

04:57.559 --> 04:59.159
that Mario doesn't know about.

04:59.228 --> 05:00.528
Let's go over there.

05:01.799 --> 05:04.767
So, red lights are flashing,
alarms are blaring.

05:04.836 --> 05:08.204
We're about 10 seconds
from a meltdown so hot

05:08.272 --> 05:11.140
it's gonna turn Belgium
into a pool of hot chocolate.

05:11.209 --> 05:12.842
And I suddenly realize,

05:12.910 --> 05:15.478
they haven't properly accounted
for the relativistic distort...

05:15.546 --> 05:16.912
Hey, what's this building's number?

05:16.981 --> 05:18.747
- I'm trying to Postmates a smoothie.
- Shh!

05:18.765 --> 05:22.667
I quickly do a few multi-dimensional
tensor calculations in my head,

05:22.736 --> 05:26.804
I push this crying guard to one side
and adjust the synchrotron.

05:27.181 --> 05:29.214
I look up at the countdown clock.

05:29.283 --> 05:30.416
5...

05:30.484 --> 05:31.617
4...

05:35.156 --> 05:37.990
You, with the phone!

05:38.059 --> 05:39.958
- What's your name?
- Alex Dunphy.

05:40.027 --> 05:42.461
Ms. Dunphy, is my story
of saving the world

05:42.530 --> 05:46.798
whilst accidently creating
three new elements boring you?

05:46.808 --> 05:49.208
Uh, no. No, no, no, no, no.
I'm so sorry, Professor.

05:49.277 --> 05:50.810
Nothing you could say
would ever bore me.

05:50.879 --> 05:52.045
I revere you.

05:52.113 --> 05:54.113
I actually went as you
last year for Halloween.

05:54.938 --> 05:56.849
Okay, it's my phone.
Don't blame my sister.

05:56.918 --> 05:59.585
Hey, Chelsea.
Gonna have to call you back.

05:59.654 --> 06:02.121
- Shut up! Shut up!
- Shut up!

06:02.190 --> 06:04.123
Excuse me, Chelsea's friend.

06:04.192 --> 06:06.092
Y-You don't look like
one of my students.

06:06.161 --> 06:08.628
Oh, thank you! That is so sweet.

06:08.697 --> 06:10.396
No. Why are you here?

06:10.465 --> 06:12.265
Oh, I have a really big
job interview today,

06:12.333 --> 06:14.367
and I need someone
to look over what I wrote for my...

06:14.436 --> 06:16.703
Yeah, we're going.
I'm taking her out. I am so sorry.

06:16.771 --> 06:19.541
What? He asked. You're being rude.

06:19.808 --> 06:20.808
Ohh!

06:20.875 --> 06:22.875
Ooh.

06:22.944 --> 06:24.444
- Very revealing.
- Get out.

06:25.974 --> 06:27.543
Claire, I'm so glad
you called.

06:27.663 --> 06:29.106
How come we've never
done this before?

06:29.263 --> 06:30.464
Because we were born
into a feud.

06:30.584 --> 06:32.794
Hatfields and McCoys,
the Sharks and Jets,

06:32.930 --> 06:36.072
the... the closet lunatic
and the closet idiot.

06:36.263 --> 06:38.513
By the way, I'm really
sorry about your dad.

06:38.538 --> 06:39.563
Thanks.

06:39.632 --> 06:42.486
Do you have any idea why he
had his ashes sent to my dad?

06:42.521 --> 06:44.803
- Probably to drive him bonkers.
- Well, it's working.

06:44.838 --> 06:46.137
That would've made him happy.

06:46.206 --> 06:49.451
Let's make a pact...
to never be like them.

06:49.486 --> 06:50.777
- I am in.
- Mm-hmm.

06:50.812 --> 06:52.928
We are two women in
a male-dominated industry.

06:52.963 --> 06:54.351
We should help each other.

06:54.386 --> 06:58.002
Actually, do you have any sources
for antique pineapple knobs?

06:58.037 --> 06:59.816
We're doing this whole colonial line...

06:59.851 --> 07:02.215
Ooh, I bet you Lazlo would know.
He's our lead designer.

07:02.250 --> 07:04.929
Everybody knows who Lazlo is.
He's a legend.

07:04.964 --> 07:06.837
Yeah, and my only employee worth a damn.

07:06.872 --> 07:08.922
Robot workers. Now, that's the future.

07:08.957 --> 07:10.743
Right! They work 24/7,

07:10.778 --> 07:12.766
and you don't have to
buy them a birthday cake.

07:12.801 --> 07:14.235
Yeah, and as they become more human,

07:14.270 --> 07:16.266
you can be like, "Hey, you,
come into my office",

07:16.301 --> 07:18.948
- and then you just go to town on them.
- Yeah.

07:20.412 --> 07:22.813
What the hell?

07:22.881 --> 07:24.581
What happened to the bodyshop?

07:24.650 --> 07:25.982
Oh, we just kept the sign.

07:26.051 --> 07:28.218
Oh, uh, so... so no M-Mario?

07:28.287 --> 07:30.520
Mnh-mnh. We're an artist collective.

07:30.589 --> 07:31.888
Jillian works in yarn,

07:31.957 --> 07:35.592
Mumford sculpts with Lego,
Duncan is a painter.

07:35.661 --> 07:36.661
May I write you a poem?

07:36.728 --> 07:39.429
- Are you kidding me?
- I told you it was a career.

07:39.511 --> 07:42.979
Um, any chance that
you have, uh, seen my son?

07:43.047 --> 07:44.280
No, I'm sorry.

07:44.349 --> 07:46.315
Oh, okay. He... He was
around here last night.

07:46.342 --> 07:48.342
He apparently wentoff with a girl
from this neighborhood.

07:48.410 --> 07:49.877
We just haven't been able
to reach him since.

07:49.945 --> 07:53.013
- Do you know the girl's name?
- No. Uh, something Latin-y.

07:53.082 --> 07:56.049
What happened to you?
You used to be Latin-y.

07:56.118 --> 07:59.652
- Can you describe her?
- Brown hair, high cheekbones...

07:59.732 --> 08:03.100
What is he gonna do,
build her out of Legos?

08:04.570 --> 08:07.471
Huh, that is surprisingly effective.

08:07.540 --> 08:09.540
Wait a minute. I know that girl.

08:09.609 --> 08:11.442
I think she works at a cupcake shop.

08:11.511 --> 08:13.043
Great. Where is it?

08:13.100 --> 08:15.000
Well, I'm not sure which one
because we have four.

08:15.069 --> 08:17.069
There's Cupcakes! with
an exclamation point,

08:17.137 --> 08:18.870
there's vegan cupcakes at Cupfakes,

08:18.939 --> 08:20.872
there's Pupcakes,
which sells cupcakes for dogs,

08:20.941 --> 08:22.876
and then there's Rick's VCR Repair.

08:22.911 --> 08:25.072
Oh, they make the best cupcakes.

08:25.472 --> 08:27.377
Stupid Max, forcing us to eat our caviar

08:27.446 --> 08:29.212
on a regular Friday morning.

08:29.281 --> 08:30.847
I can't even enjoy
the symphony of flavors,

08:30.916 --> 08:32.881
or the... or the way
that it melts in my mouth.

08:32.951 --> 08:35.051
Why don't you just wash it down
with whatever wine's left.

08:35.120 --> 08:36.120
Yeah, why don't I.

08:36.188 --> 08:37.352
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

08:39.089 --> 08:40.621
Mmm, and, of course, you know what?

08:40.691 --> 08:42.123
It pairs perfectly.

08:42.192 --> 08:45.427
I-I cannot believe I'm having one of the
best meals of my life

08:45.495 --> 08:46.795
and we're not even celebrating anything.

08:46.863 --> 08:47.996
Yeah, thanks, Max!

08:48.065 --> 08:49.631
- Thank you, Max.
- Thank you, Max.

08:50.901 --> 08:51.901
Mmm...

08:54.137 --> 08:56.071
Cam, is it... is it... is it possible

08:56.139 --> 08:57.806
that we're actually enjoying ourselves

08:57.874 --> 08:59.540
and... and that Max was right?

08:59.584 --> 09:01.050
Maybe we do defer enjoyment.

09:01.119 --> 09:03.019
All those unspent frequent flyer miles,

09:03.088 --> 09:04.654
the boots that
I have waited so long to wear

09:04.722 --> 09:05.988
that they're no longer in style,

09:06.057 --> 09:08.057
the... the... the surfboards

09:08.159 --> 09:09.849
that we've never used because it just

09:09.874 --> 09:11.494
"had to be the perfect beach day".

09:13.098 --> 09:14.464
What are you doing?

09:14.533 --> 09:16.212
- Mitchell...
- I'm lighting it.

09:16.247 --> 09:17.800
- No!
- I'm lighting it!

09:17.835 --> 09:19.235
No, that is our
monogrammed wedding candle,

09:19.304 --> 09:20.603
and we're supposed to save it.

09:20.672 --> 09:22.705
For what, Cam?

09:22.774 --> 09:24.107
- I don't know!
- You don't know.

09:24.175 --> 09:25.675
- I don't.
- You don't know.

09:25.744 --> 09:28.211
Ohh... look at it.

09:28.280 --> 09:31.579
Smells like eternal love.

09:31.614 --> 09:34.268
- Aww...oh.
- O-kay.

09:35.031 --> 09:36.880
Why are you always in my office?

09:36.949 --> 09:38.815
I do my best work in here.

09:38.884 --> 09:40.917
I've been trying to get into his head.

09:40.986 --> 09:42.586
I even brought his favorite lunch...

09:42.655 --> 09:44.687
shrimp cocktail and bourbon.

09:44.722 --> 09:46.789
Or that's just what you have for
lunch every day.

09:46.824 --> 09:48.328
That's another thing Earl stole from me!

09:48.363 --> 09:49.764
What did you find out?

09:49.799 --> 09:52.328
First of all, Shirl doesn't
know anything about the ashes.

09:52.376 --> 09:54.676
And second, we're not gonna be
a part of your little feud anymore.

09:54.745 --> 09:56.845
- We're gonna be friends.
- She's playing you!

09:56.914 --> 09:58.480
- No...
- Let me ask you a question.

09:58.549 --> 10:01.185
Did you tell her we're
bidding on Belmont Gardens?

10:01.210 --> 10:02.270
No. Why?

10:02.305 --> 10:04.219
Because 15 minutes ago,
I got a phone call

10:04.288 --> 10:06.470
saying just out of the blue,

10:06.505 --> 10:09.557
Closets Closets Closets Closets
is bidding against us.

10:09.651 --> 10:11.451
Did she see your proposal?

10:11.520 --> 10:13.481
Yes, Dad! I'm quite sure

10:13.516 --> 10:15.566
she rifled through my bag
when I was in the bathroom.

10:15.601 --> 10:17.744
You went to the bathroom? Why don't
you just give her the company?!

10:17.769 --> 10:18.941
Oh, God.

10:20.358 --> 10:22.625
- Bingo! Ketchup!
- What does that prove?

10:22.694 --> 10:25.328
- Did she have ketchup for lunch?
- She had... French fries.

10:25.397 --> 10:26.863
There's your smoking gun.

10:26.932 --> 10:30.544
Margaret? I'm gonna need fries
and ketchup to get in Shirl's head.

10:30.579 --> 10:31.915
No! No, Shirl wouldn't have done this.

10:31.950 --> 10:33.075
Um, bad news.

10:33.110 --> 10:35.404
Uh, we finally tracked down
those pineapple knobs,

10:35.475 --> 10:37.215
but they were all
just bought up by Closets...

10:37.244 --> 10:38.244
- No.
- ...Closets...

10:38.311 --> 10:40.911
- No, Margaret!
- ...Closets Closets.

10:42.282 --> 10:43.881
Shirl screwed me.

10:43.950 --> 10:45.350
You know what you have to do?

10:45.418 --> 10:46.651
You've got to hit her where it hurts.

10:46.720 --> 10:49.921
- What does she value most?
- Lazlo.

10:50.478 --> 10:53.645
I don't think you understand
how humiliating that was for me.

10:53.714 --> 10:55.848
There are parts of me
that will never uncringe.

10:55.916 --> 10:59.251
Oh, my God!
So I interrupted some boring story.

10:59.320 --> 11:02.488
Dr. Arvin Fennerman
is a two-time Vanderkoff Grant winner...

11:02.556 --> 11:04.523
one for philosophy
and one for geometry.

11:04.592 --> 11:05.809
You can't put him into a box because...

11:05.834 --> 11:07.364
Could you please just read my sample?

11:07.399 --> 11:11.116
This job is important to me.
This is my one shot at a real career.

11:11.151 --> 11:12.731
Fine, I'll read it. And "real career"?

11:12.800 --> 11:15.090
I've seen
this NERP business.

11:15.125 --> 11:17.008
Nicole Rosemary Page seems bonkers.

11:17.043 --> 11:18.936
Didn't she get in trouble
for cannibalism?

11:18.971 --> 11:21.544
No. Turns out there are no laws against

11:21.579 --> 11:24.923
eating your own appendix,
and it does help with fine lines.

11:24.958 --> 11:28.496
But she's a success story.
Child star, Bond girl,

11:28.499 --> 11:31.257
indie darling before she lost all her
money to a Fonzie scheme.

11:31.292 --> 11:33.887
- Don't you mean Ponzi scheme?
- Sadly, no.

11:33.922 --> 11:36.437
So, out of desperation,
she invented NERP,

11:36.472 --> 11:38.697
and next thing you know... boom! Empire.

11:38.732 --> 11:40.187
I just want to be
a part of something great.

11:40.243 --> 11:43.149
